{"entity": "Regulation (EU) 2016/679", "type": "content", "description": "Regulation (EU) 2016/679, commonly known as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), is a regulation of the European Parliament and the Council of the European Union. It serves as a comprehensive Union data protection law designed to safeguard the fundamental right to the protection of personal data and privacy. The regulation governs the processing of personal data, mandating transparency and specific governance practices to protect the rights and freedoms of data subjects.

The regulation provides critical legal definitions for personal data, non-personal data, and profiling, the latter of which is specifically defined in Article 4, point (4). It establishes a framework for identifying high risks to the rights and freedoms of data subjects and specifies conditions for using data within AI regulatory sandboxes. Additionally, under this regulation, supervisory authorities may be designated as market surveillance authorities.

