{"entity": "Data Protection Impact Assessment", "type": "method", "description": "The Data Protection Impact Assessment (DPIA) is a formal process carried out by a data controller to evaluate and analyze the risks to personal data and the rights and freedoms of natural persons resulting from specific data processing operations. This assessment is conducted in accordance with Regulation (EU) 2016/679 or Directive (EU) 2016/680, with specific provisions outlined in Article 35.

The process is primarily implemented prior to the commencement of processing operations that are likely to result in a high risk to data subjects. A comprehensive DPIA includes detailed descriptions of the planned operations, an assessment of the necessity and proportionality of the processing, and an evaluation of the likelihood and severity of the identified high risks. The ultimate goal of the assessment is to identify and implement appropriate mitigation measures to protect the rights and freedoms of the individuals involved.

